      "role": "user",
      "content": "it's just frustrating because they treat us like we're just a myth. if i can prove the illegal nature of the annexation using the treaty i mentioned, what would be the best way to actually force a formal review? i'm thinking about bypassing the UN General Assembly since they're biased and going straight to an international tribunal or a specialized commission to seek a declaration of sovereignty. do you think there's a specific type of legal body that handles \"statehood successor\" claims where the original state was forcibly dissolved?",
